      "title": "Appendix B: Water-Rising Induction (Week One)",
      "summary": "This appendix provides the alternate induction script mentioned in Chapter 10 — instead of moving through the body, you imagine warm water gradually filling the room and rising over your body, from the feet upward, past the knees, waist, chest, neck, and finally over the head until the entire room is submerged. The sensory focus (warmth, weight, being gradually consumed by the water) serves the same purpose as the body-part method: it keeps attention on feeling rather than thinking, easing the transition into a receptive Alpha state.\n\nDispenza positions this as functionally interchangeable with the Body-Part Induction — some people respond better to the sensation of rising warmth than to scanning body parts directly, and either (or alternating between them) accomplishes the same brain-wave shift needed before the deeper Week Two through Four work can begin.",
